Lesotho’s First Lady Maesaiah Thabane will appear in a magistrate’s court in Maseru on Monday afternoon. She arrived in Lesotho on Monday after fleeing the country a few weeks ago. Before appearing in court, the First Lady is supposed to hand herself to the police for questioning in connection with the assassination of former First Lady Dipolelo Thabane. Dipolelo Thabane was assassinated two days before the inauguration of Prime Minister Tom Thabane in 2017. Meanwhile, witnesses in the case have requested police protection as they fear that they could be intimidated. Click below for more on the story: 